<TITLE> Graft busters quiz Tarique in jail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 3 (bdnews24.com) Three members of an anti-crime taskforce questioned BNP senior joint secretary general Tarique Rahman in Dhaka Central Jail Tuesday. The members of the taskforce quizzed former prime minister Khaleda Zia's son from 4pm to 5.45pm. Jail authorities said the three members of the national committee on serious crime who arrived at the main gate 3.45pm were deputy director of the Anticorruption Commission Zahurul Huda, income tax official Abdus Samad Al Azad and Major Redwan Ahmed Khan. Deputy inspector general (prisons) Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com, "The taskforce members began grilling Tarique Rahman from 4 pm in the doctor's room inside the main gate of the jail." "Half an hour after the interrogation began Tarique Rahman's lawyer advocate Ahmed Azam Khan appeared there," he said. "After the questioning the taskforce members left the jail at 5.45 pm." ACC deputy director Zahurul Huda told bdnews24.com, "We questioned Tarique Rahman to verify the authenticity of the wealth report he submitted as part of our investigation. I am not in a position to say anything more." Tarique's lawyer who was present during the questioning told bdnews24.com, "The taskforce members discussed in detail the wealth report Tarique Rahman had submitted to the Anticorruption Commission. They talked in a very open manner." He also said Tarique had cooperated fully through the interview. Anticorruption officers went to Mahbub Bhaban in Dhanmondi on July 1 to question Tarique's wife Dr Jobaida Rahman and his mother-in-law Syeda Iqbalmand Banu. bdnews2
